devdoc.details: :   Upgradeable ERC721 Contract. Final proposed implementation (XFO), Rinkeby. Purpose built for optmization over the Zora V1 contracts. isian (iain nash) of Zora.  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

burn(uint256).details: burns given tokenId, restrited to owner and creator (when owned)

params._tokenId: uint256 identifier of token to burn

creator(uint256).details: basic public getter method for creator

params._tokenId: uint256 identifier of token to get creator for

initialize(string,string).details: Initializes contract with default values, for upgradeable proxy purposes

mint((string,string,address,address,uint.details: mints a new token to allowlisted msg.sender with a valid merkle proof. params can and should be changed to calldata for gas efficiency. rename to "allowlist"

params._proof: bytes32[] merkle proof of artist wallet.  this is created off-chain.  e.g (proof = tree.getHexProof(keccak256(address)))

returns._0: uint256 tokenId of minted token (useful since we are not using Enumerable)

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._salePrice: uint256 final sale price of token used to calculate royalty payout
params._tokenId: uint256 token id corresponding to the token of which to get royalty information

royaltyPayoutAddress(uint256).details: basic public getter method for royalty payout address

params._tokenId: uint256 identifier of token to get royalty payout address for

returns._0: address royalty payout address of given tokenId

params.interfaceId: bytes4 id of interface to check

tokenContentURI(uint256).details: basic public getter method for content URI

params._tokenId: uint256 identifier of token to get content URI for

returns._0: string content URI for given tokenId

tokenURI(uint256).details: override function, returns metadataURI of token stored in tokenData

params._tokenId: uint256 token id corresponding to the token of which to get metadata from

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateContentURI(uint256,string).details: access controlled function, restricted to owner/admim.

params._contentURI: string containing new/updated media content (subject to change, new EIP)
params._tokenId: uint256 token id corresponding to the token to update

updateCreator(uint256,address).details: access controlled function, restricted to owner/admim. used in case of compromised artist wallet.

params._creator: address new creator of the token
params._tokenId: uint256 token id corresponding to the token to update

updateMetadataURI(uint256,string).details: access controlled, restricted to contract owner/admin or the creator of the token

params._metadataURI: string containing new/updated metadata (e.g IPFS URI pointing to metadata.json)
params._tokenId: uint256 token id corresponding to the token to update

updateRoot(bytes32).details: access controlled function, restricted to owner/admim.

params._newRoot: bytes32 containing the new root hash, generated off-chain

updateRoyaltyInfo(uint256,address).details: access controlled to owner only, subject to change.  this function allows for emergency royalty control (i.e compromised wallet)

params._royaltyPayoutAddress: address of new royalty payout address
params._tokenId: uint256 token id corresponding to the token of which to update royalty payout
